sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor M as Merchant or Admin
    participant API as Refund Service
    participant DB as MySQL
    participant LEDGER as Cashback Ledger
    participant GW as Payment Gateway
    participant SETTLE as Settlement Job

    M->>API: Initiate refund for order O
    API->>DB: SELECT order with payment and cashback context
    DB-->>API: Order, payment, lots earned from this payment, redemptions applied to this payment

    API->>API: Compute payable_total as order total minus cashback redeemed on this order
    API->>API: Only the gateway portion is refundable

    API->>GW: Refund payable_total
    GW-->>API: Refund accepted

    API->>DB: BEGIN
    API->>DB: UPDATE payment - set is_refund to true and store refund metadata

    Note over API: Reverse only the Vast fees on lots earned from this payment.<br/>Lots and redemptions are not modified.

    loop For each cashback lot tied to the refunded payment
        API->>LEDGER: INSERT reverse_vast_fee event with vast_fee_amount, lot_id, payment_id
    end

    API->>DB: COMMIT

    Note over API: Used cashback stays consumed and is non-refundable.<br/>Earned cashback stays in the customer wallet.<br/>Customer balance is unchanged by the refund.

    API-->>M: Refund successful with summary of fees reversed

    Note over SETTLE: Next settlement cycle picks up reverse_vast_fee events<br/>and posts merchant credits to financial_transactions.

    SETTLE->>LEDGER: Read reverse_vast_fee events since last payout
    SETTLE->>DB: INSERT credits to financial_transactions for affected merchants
